OL,3,CWhy humidity levels could make the 40C
OL,4,Cheatwave feel even hotter
OL,6,FHumidity is the general term for
OL,7,Fmoisture in the air.
OL,9,FWhen the air is humid, it contains a
OL,10,Frelatively high amount of water vapour.
OL,12,FThis is generally associated with
OL,13,Fsomething called a higher dew point,
OL,14,Fwhich is the temperature the air must
OL,15,Fbe cooled to for condensation to
OL,16,Fbegin. For example, a higher dew point
OL,17,Fof 24C will create a very oppressive
OL,18,Fand tropical feeling.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
