OL,3,CWhy humidity levels could make the 40C
OL,4,Cheatwave feel even hotter
OL,6,FWhen it's humid, the air is already so
OL,7,Ffull of water that it can't take in
OL,8,Fmore moisture - for example, sweat -
OL,9,Fas a result, it evaporates more slowly.
OL,11,FThat means less heat is removed from
OL,12,Fthe body, and we sweat more, making it
OL,13,Ffeel increasingly uncomfortable with
OL,14,Foverheating likely.
OL,16,FHow humid will it be over the next few
OL,17,Fdays?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
